net.cabezudo.json.values

Class JSONObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.cabezudo.json.JSONElement
      • net.cabezudo.json.values.JSONValue<JSONObject>
        • net.cabezudo.json.values.JSONObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<JSONObject>, java.lang.Iterable<JSONPair>, JSONable

    public class JSONObject
extends JSONValue<JSONObject>
implements java.lang.Iterable<JSONPair>
    A JSONObject is an object extended from JSONValue object in order to represent a JSON object that can be used to create JSON structures.

    A JSONObject is a list of JSONPair objects that represent the JSON object structure.

        public JSONObject(java.lang.Object object)

        The object must have the properties annotated with JSONProperty in order to be used as a JSON object property. If the object is Iterable or the object is a primitive array the method throws a JSONConvertionException.

        Parameters:
        object - a POJO Object.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(JSONObject jsonObject)
        Compare two JSONObject objects.

        The rules for comparison are the next:

        The method first compares the number of properties and returns a value less than 0 if this JSONObject has less properties than the argument; and a value greater than 0 if this JSONObject has more properties than the argument.

        If the the number of properties comparison is 0 then compare the keys in natural order. Compare one at a time the keys and the result is a negative integer if the property name of this JSONObject object lexicographically precedes the property name of the argument JSONObject object. The result is a positive integer if the property of this JSONObject object lexicographically follows the argument property name in the same position. The result is zero if all the property names are equal and in the same order.

        If the properties names are the same, compare the values. The method uses the property order to compare the values. Compare one at a time the values and the result is a negative integer if the property value of this JSONObject object is less than the property value of the argument JSONObject object for the same property. The result is a positive integer if the property value of this JSONObject object is greater than the property value of the argument JSONObject object for the same property. The result is zero if the property values are equal for all the properties.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<JSONObject>
        Parameters:
        jsonObject - the JSONObject to be compared.
        Returns:
        the value 0 if this JSONObject is equal to the argument JSONObject; a value less than 0 if this JSONObject is less (using the rules) than the argument JSONObject object; and a value greater than 0 if this JSONObject object is greater (using the rules) than the argument JSONObject.
